HUMPHREY Nzima is hustling by turning old beer and cold drink cans into kids’ toys. He told Daily Sun he started the small project in December after he had been job hunting since 2009. when he passed matric. Humphrey (32) from Dingleydale, outside Acornhoek in Mpumalanga, said: he went around collecting cans of beer and cold drinks in the street. “I turned the old cans into nice toys using wires and paint.  I sell them in my area, as well as in Acornhoek, Dwarsloop, Bushbuckridge and Thulamahashe Shopping Malls.I sell each toy for R30 to R40. READ: MADALA’S FLOWER POTS A HIT EKASI! “I can make up to R500 in a day. I can now look after my  I also make Toyota Quantum and bicycle toys. When people see rubbish after drinking, I see money. So I don’t go to bed on an empty stomach anymore.three kids and my mum.” And I am also proud as I am keeping the environment clean,” he said.  Humphrey’s friend, Mfundo Shabangu (20) said: “I am very proud of him. He’s a friend indeed. I am in matric, so when I am not studying  I go around with him selling the toys so I can get pocket money.” Customer Vusi Selabe (33) said he bought three Quantum taxis as well a as bicycle toys for his two boys. “They are nice and we are proud to support our local growing market,” he said.